Currently, we can set the `readerName` by 
```java
 public ReaderBuilder<T> readerName(String readerName) {
        conf.setReaderName(readerName);
        return this;
    }
```
But  `readerName` is used for setting  consumerName (not subscription name) of the internal subscription 
```java
if (readerConfiguration.getReaderName() != null) {
            consumerConfiguration.setConsumerName(readerConfiguration.getReaderName());
        }
```
I think we can set the subscription name  by : 
1. if set the `readerName`, we can set the subcription name to `readerName`
2. if not set the `readerName`, we use the origin logic which is  reader- or "multiTopicsReader-"  combine with a random part.

